<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E88FF0748F75052FECEFE94" lastPageId="199" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418E88FF0748F75052FECEFE94" blockId="198.[151,1436,1882,2014]" lastBlockId="199.[151,1436,151,464]" lastPageId="199" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E88FF0648F75052FEE4F867" bold="true" box="[199,321,1918,1943]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E88FF06497C5052FE05F866" box="[332,416,1918,1942]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Female</emphasis>
: (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E88FF06498D5052FDF6F866" box="[445,595,1918,1943]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
Plate 52A 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E88FF064A015053FD9AF867" bold="true" box="[561,575,1919,1943]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">–</emphasis>
D
</figureCitation>
): fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E88FF064B275052FC22F866" box="[791,903,1918,1942]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Plate 52E</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; pronotum with a distinct anterior collar and a posterior disc separated by a transverse impression (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E88FF064C04508EFB00F84A" box="[1076,1189,1954,1978]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Plate 52A</figureCitation>
); posterior surface of pronotum swollen and with a flat surface; pronotal tubercle present; fore wing with three cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal, median and submedian) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E89FF074AE857BBFCECFF5F" box="[728,841,151,175]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Plate 52G</figureCitation>
), stigmal vein and pterostigma present (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E89FF074D2A57BBFA2EFF5F" box="[1306,1419,151,175]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Plate 52G</figureCitation>
), distal part of stigmal vein much longer than proximal part (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E89FF074B705790FC77FF24" box="[832,978,188,212]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Plate 52E, G</figureCitation>
) and media vein (M) partly present and strongly sclerotized (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E89FF0749B657F3FE53FF07" box="[390,502,223,247]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Plate 52H</figureCitation>
); protarsus chelate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E89FF074AD057F3FCCAFF07" box="[736,879,223,247]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Plate 52C, F</figureCitation>
); chela without rudimentary claw; enlarged claw not spatulate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E89FF07490C5628FE0BFEEC" box="[316,430,260,284]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Plate 52H</figureCitation>
); inner side of enlarged claw with a row of at least 4 bristles, all longer than greatest breadth of enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E89FF07498A560BFD8DFECF" box="[442,552,295,319]" captionStart="PLATE 52" captionStartId="197.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,201,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-61@197.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="197" captionText="PLATE 52. Burmanteon olmii, holotype. A. Lateral view. Length 1.6 mm. B. Head and antenna. C, D. Ventral view. E. Fore wing. F. Chela. G. Fore wing (basalmost portion of wing not illustrated) (from Engel, 2003). H. Chela (from Engel, 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278554/files/figure.png" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Plate 52H</figureCitation>
); protrochanter short and not slender; epicnemium not distinct; tibial spurs 1/1/ 2. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E89FF0748835660FF49FE94" box="[179,236,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Male</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E89FF0748F75643FE2BFE5C" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="007606418E89FF0748F75643FD54FE77" blockId="199.[151,1436,151,464]" box="[199,753,367,392]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E89FF0748F75643FEC5FE78" bold="true" box="[199,352,367,392]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Distribution.</emphasis>
Present only in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E89FF074A0F5643FD48FE77" box="[575,749,367,391]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E89FF0748F756B8FE2BFE5C" blockId="199.[151,1436,151,464]" box="[199,398,404,428]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E89FF0748F756B8FEB4FE5C" bold="true" box="[199,273,404,428]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Hosts.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E89FF0748F75694FD1CFE3F" box="[199,697,439,464]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="007606418E89FF0748F75694FD1CFE3F" blockId="199.[151,1436,151,464]" box="[199,697,439,464]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E89FF0748F75694FED1FE20" bold="true" box="[199,372,439,464]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">World species.</emphasis>
One fossil species is known.
</paragraph>
